<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>SPICER 14-INCH (356 MM) AND 15 1/2-INCH (394 MM) TWO-PLATE, PULL-TYPE CLUTCH - REMOVE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REMOVE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
            <title>TRANSMISSION</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>When removing the transmission and drive shaft, use a sling or jack to maintain alignment (
                        <hotlnk xrefid="f1100113">Figure 13</hotlnk>). Do not let the transmission drop or hang
                        unsupported in the splined hubs of the clutch discs. Taking these precautions will prevent
                        bending and distortion of the clutch discs.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1100113" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1100113" filename="../figg11/g1100113.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 13. Maintain Alignment of Transmission</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>Disconnect the external clutch linkage before pulling the transmission free (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1100114">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1100114" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1100114" filename="../figg11/g1100114.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 14. Disconnect External Clutch Linkage</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When the vehicle is equipped with a torque limiting clutch brake, note whether the small
                        diameter of the clutch brake faces the engine or the transmission.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
